==English==
===Etymology===
French [[baton]], corrupted as bastin in English. ''(Cf. [[bastion]].)''
===Noun===
'''bastinado'''
#a form of [[corporal punishment]] in which the bare [[soles]] of the feet are beaten with a stick or [[truncheon]].

===Verb===
#to punish someone by beating someone on the bare soles of the feet, usign a stick or truncheon.
====Inflected forms====
{{top}}
*Past tense: ''bastinadoed''/''bastinado'd''
*Present tense: ''bastinado'', ''bastinadoes''
*Present habitual: ''bastinadoing''
